 need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"important"},{"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI","type":"heading","text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook clone"},{"type":"text","text":" for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instant copies."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open Spooktacular."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"+"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" button or press "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cmd+N","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Create","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into a new VM bundle.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Managing VMs","anchor":"Managing-VMs"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CapacityCheck","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for details."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Important","style":"important"},{"type":"heading","text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts","anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"bash","code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"ssh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. See "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" for provisioning strategies and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doc:Provisioning"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed guidance."}]},{"type":"heading","text":"EC2 Mac Setup","anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"release. See ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","type":"reference"},{"text":" for the planned architecture.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/gettingstarted"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/ProvisioningMode":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ProvisioningMode"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The strategy for executing a user-data script on a VM."}],"title":"ProvisioningMode","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ProvisioningMode"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/provisioningmode","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","type":"topic"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/KubernetesGuide":{"title":"Kubernetes Integration","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/kubernetesguide","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manage macOS virtual machines as Kubernetes resources using the MacOSVM custom resource definition."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/EC2MacDeployment":{"abstract":[{"text":"Run Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac dedicated hosts to double your macOS CI capacity.","type":"text"}],"title":"Deploying on EC2 Mac","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/ec2macdeployment","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment"},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/VirtualMachineConfiguration":{"abstract":[{"text":"Builds ","type":"text"},{"code":"VZVirtualMachineConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" objects from a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecif